    "id": 157199165,
    "user": {
      "login": "as-cii",
      "id": 482957,
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/482957?v=3",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/as-cii",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/as-cii",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/as-cii/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/as-cii/following{/other_user}",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/as-cii/gists{/gist_id}",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/as-cii/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/as-cii/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/as-cii/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/as-cii/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/as-cii/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/as-cii/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": true
    },
    "created_at": "2015-11-16T22:50:12Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-11-16T22:50:12Z",
    "body": "Looking at those issues it would seem like this is not related just to a specific platform: given that the Slack team is observing similar issues too, I'd agree that this could be related to a Chromium :bug:.\n\nSo, based on @paulcbetts's investigation, there are a couple of things we should probably do to fix this:\n1. Make sure we're running the latest Squirrel version. It seems like AppCompat was messing with DPI stuff and this has been fixed in the last versions (https://github.com/Squirrel/Squirrel.Windows/pull/478)\n2. Upgrade Electron's Chromium Version. It seems like the Chromium team is aware of this problem and they've been discussing it [over here](https://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=484400): unfortunately, a fix hasn't landed yet, so I _think_ the only two options here would be to:\n   - Wait for a fix to land on the next Chrome versions;\n   - Or, if that's not going to happen anytime soon, patch libchromiumcontent ourselves;\n\nAs far as I can tell, they're already working on a fix (https://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=485650) and the plan is to :shipit: in time for Chrome 49.\n\n@zcbenz: I am going to reopen this issue, but I'd like to hear your thoughts about it :thought_balloon:. From the changelogs it's not clear if some sort of fix has been shipped on Chrome 48, but it's probably worth having a :eyes: at it.\n"
  },
