    "created_at": "2016-02-22T16:06:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-02-22T16:07:08Z",
    "body": "At least for me, Chrome 47/48 hasn't fixed the issue. Only the code is blurry, which I fixed with --force-device-scale-factor=1, which has the unfortunate side effect of making the menu bar and file tree smaller than it should be. I've noticed this issue with a few websites in Chrome such as Google Drive so I've switched to using Firefox for editing stuff there.\n\nI'm running Windows 8.1 64bit on a 1920x1080 screen at whatever Larger scaling is (I 'think' it may be 1.5 but honestly I'm not sure). Before writing this I downloaded the Atom installer and reinstalled it, to no avail.\n\nIf this is the wrong place to put this, and I was supposed to create a new issue, I'm sorry and put it here because it seems this was never really resolved for Windows.\n"
  },
